	   <tr><td colspan=2>As to successful kiting... DO NOT LISTEN TO YOUR FRIEND that you arent pushing enough.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Kiting takes a certain &quot;nack&quot;. I know folks who aren't successful kiting more than 3 mobs.  They are comfortable with that, but when they try again to get 4 mobs they get clobbered.  Bottem line is do what is comfortable for you.  Start with 2 mobs a few times then snare 3 and kite 3 a few times.  Try 4 then 5. You will have a comfort level if its 2 or 3 or 4 just go with it.  EW in the Icefang area is perfect for figuring out your comfort level.  Keeping control of the Kite is paramont.  Lack of control means you and more importantly OTHER people could die.  That only serves to give us all a bad Rep.<br><br><br>Ya EW rocks for Kite Training. I never liked the bridge area too many people and too many dervishes ect to dodge. In the SW part of the zone are 2 huts where you find Icefang the giant killing wolf.  The huts are a  very short run SE of the Kael zoneline(be carefull of the drop of the ramp-make sure you enter the ramp from the front- the fall is litteraly a killer).<br><br>NO CRITTERS PATH NEAR THE HUTS... actually there is a ridge south of the huts the extends east almost to the Dragon platform that marks the entrance to Sleeper Tomb.  Between that ridge and the ocean cliff no mobs path either and is an AWESOME long undisturbed kite area.  The huts offer some PRIME hunting areas litterally next door.  To the west is a huge pod of Walrus that stay blue till about 48-9.  There are tons of Mammoths and Rhinos also that stay blue till 50-52 to the north and northeast. 2 types of giants that can also be kited or root/DOTed roam in the vacinity... Scout and Savage Frost giants.  They have the best loot occasional FS weapons 4-7pp, toes 9-10pp, and Beards(5 dose Storm Strength)11pp.  Taking the giants that are foolish enough to wander in your sight will help you get good faction with the Claws of Veeshan the dragons in several higher level druid kiting areas.<br><br>The area around the dragon platform is also a good place to med and kite around. My ranger probably operated from here when a dru moved into the hut area.  My Ranger had a blast in this zone kiting Giants and I am now with my Druid.  I bind next to the fire by Icefang.  Port to POK sell and bank at the Druid bank and gate back.<br><br>PS. If you are kiting or root/ DOTing Giants and get in trouble Icefang will help you if you run the gaint near him.  He acts like a guard to gaints as they are KOS to him.<br><br>Valinatt 53 Ranger<br>Decceon 36 Druid<br>Beowulv 40 Druid(retired)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed May  7 09:43:49 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
