	   <tr><td colspan=2>umm When Druids talk about kiting the usually mean snaring multiple mobs running them in a circle or allow them to bunch up as the wack his/her DS ... then pull the whole group that are practically standing on top of each other and then cast LIGHTNING STRIKE... a level 34 AOE area of effect 185-188DD that wacks all mobs at the same time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Run a ways stop cast run cast till they all die in the last spectacular explosion( unless one resisted then you finish of with combust or some other single target DD).  Casting any DOT would be a waste of mana and time.  <br><br>You certainly can multi root/dot and many do that very well, but the golden time in any druids life is from 34-49(when you get the ungrade to lightning strike) when critters to kite are everywhere and XP flows like, well, easily.  WAY WAY more efficient than DOTing 4 mobs and running around. <br><br>Give it a try...<br><br>Valiantt 53 Ranger<br>Decceon 37 Druid<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
